		<rdf:_4>
	<Project rdf:about="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::4">
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="./4/"/>
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="#bjmns:4"/>
		<identifier rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#NCName">piwhall</identifier>
		<fullTitle xml:lang="en">Project Alchemy</fullTitle>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/works/13154660"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/works/14075923"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/hubs/16ae8da271effbf3944940c8fd69a176"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/works/13445862"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/hubs/de7f79fdf094c4fafdca4bb4884a7d79"/>
		<dc:abstract rdf:parseType="Resource">
			<contents rdf:parseType="Literal"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en" xml:lang="en">
	<p>Follows an apprentice alchemist and his discovery of the existence of demons on another plane of existence.  For the sake of spellcasting, I invented an alternate Old English language, (termed “the Old Language”; see <a href="https://go.KIBI.family/Corpora/langdev.xyz,2017/cpe/oen/" resource="tag:langdev.xyz,2017:cpe:oen"><code>langdev:cpe:oen</code></a>), marking the beginnings of my interest in language development.</p>
</div></contents>
		</dc:abstract>
