	</Volume>
		</includes>
		<includes>
	<Volume rdf:about="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::6:Θ">
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="./6/Θ/"/>
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="#bjmns:6:Θ"/>
		<identifier rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#NCName">Θ</identifier>
		<index rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#NCName">Θ</index>
		<fullTitle xml:lang="en">The Legend of Ilia: Theta</fullTitle>
		<abbreviatedTitle xml:lang="en">Theta</abbreviatedTitle>
		<dc:abstract rdf:parseType="Resource">
			<contents rdf:parseType="Literal"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en" xml:lang="en">
	<p>I quite liked the decision to begin this story from the monsters’ perspective at the time.  As I recall, it was going to focus much more heavily on monster (i.e., blin) culture and their feelings regarding the events of <a href="http://id.loc.gov/resources/hubs/4a3df29ff3a489e191b1df29386dd28b"><code>lcbh:4a3df29ff3a489e191b1df29386dd28b</code></a>, with perhaps some kind of animosity towards Link due to the actions of his previous incarnation.</p>
</div></contents>
		</dc:abstract>
