		<rdf:_7>
	<Project rdf:about="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::7">
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="./7/"/>
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="#bjmns:7"/>
		<identifier rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#NCName">forces</identifier>
		<fullTitle xml:lang="en">Tyneland</fullTitle>
		<abbreviatedTitle xml:lang="en">c(x)</abbreviatedTitle>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/hubs/4a3df29ff3a489e191b1df29386dd28b"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/hubs/4c63f94b899a65e4bae19a5eadcb16ed"/>
		<dc:abstract rdf:parseType="Resource">
			<contents rdf:parseType="Literal"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en" xml:lang="en">
	<p>A reworking of <a href="https://go.KIBI.family/Corpora/bjmns.tumblr.com,2013/6/" resource="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::6"><code>bjmns:6</code></a> into more original content.  In some cases the <a href="http://id.loc.gov/resources/hubs/4a3df29ff3a489e191b1df29386dd28b"><code>lcbh:4a3df29ff3a489e191b1df29386dd28b</code></a> influence is more apparent; others are more of an exploration of ideas I had which took things in a different direction.  Most of these stories involve “Bearers” of “Forces” in some fashion; this concept would eventually mature into <a href="https://go.KIBI.family/Corpora/bjmns.tumblr.com,2013/15/" resource="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::15"><code>bjmns:15</code></a>.</p>
	<p>I was reading <a href="http://id.loc.gov/resources/hubs/4c63f94b899a65e4bae19a5eadcb16ed"><code>lcbh:4c63f94b899a65e4bae19a5eadcb16ed</code></a> at the time although I am not sure the influence is necessarily apparent.</p>
</div></contents>
		</dc:abstract>
		<includes>
	<Volume rdf:about="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::7:1">
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="./7/1/"/>
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="#bjmns:7:1"/>
		<index rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">1</index>
		<includes>
	<Version rdf:about="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::7:1:River">
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="./7/1/River/"/>
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="#bjmns:7:1:River"/>
		<identifier rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#NCName">River</identifier>
		<index rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#NCName">River</index>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/works/19629392"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/works/14151808"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/works/13526732"/>
		<dc:abstract rdf:parseType="Resource">
			<contents rdf:parseType="Literal"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en" xml:lang="en">
	<p>Aside from developing the <a href="https://go.KIBI.family/Corpora/bjmns.tumblr.com,2013/6/Α/" resource="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::6:Α"><code>bjmns:6:Α</code></a> concept that the [Tri]Force manifests itself in Bearers when they would otherwise perish, this story is notable for having both slice‐of‐life elements and an actual plot!  Or, well, the beginnings of one, anyway.</p>
	<p>I’m going to claim that the protagonist losing his memory was inspired by <a href="http://id.loc.gov/resources/works/19629392"><code>lcbw:19629392</code></a> because that seems about right.</p>
</div></contents>
		</dc:abstract>
		<includes>
