		</includes>
		<includes>
	<Version rdf:about="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::7:1:0">
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="./7/1/0/"/>
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="#bjmns:7:1:0"/>
		<index rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">0</index>
		<fullTitle xml:lang="en">Trials</fullTitle>
		<dc:abstract rdf:parseType="Resource">
			<contents rdf:parseType="Literal"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en" xml:lang="en">
	<p>This was my very first attempt at writing an original fantasy novel in the vein of <a href="https://go.KIBI.family/Corpora/bjmns.tumblr.com,2013/6/" resource="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::6"><code>bjmns:6</code></a> and it is a similar sort of day‐in‐the‐life drama that goes absolutely nowhere.</p>
</div></contents>
		</dc:abstract>
		<includes>
	<Draft rdf:about="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::7:1:0:1">
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="./7/1/0/1/"/>
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="#bjmns:7:1:0:1"/>
		<index rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">1</index>
		<fullTitle xml:lang="en">Tyneland: Trial 1</fullTitle>
		<abbreviatedTitle xml:lang="en">Trial 1</abbreviatedTitle>
		<isPublishedAs>
	<dcmitype:Text rdf:about="./7/1/0/1/text.html">
		<dc:format>
	<dc:FileFormat>
		<dc:identifier rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">text/html</dc:identifier>
	</dc:FileFormat>
		</dc:format>
	</dcmitype:Text>
		</isPublishedAs>
		<isPublishedAs>
	<dcmitype:Text rdf:about="./7/1/0/1/text.rtf">
		<dc:format>
	<dc:FileFormat>
		<dc:identifier rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">application/rtf</dc:identifier>
	</dc:FileFormat>
		</dc:format>
	</dcmitype:Text>
		</isPublishedAs>
	</Draft>
		</includes>
	</Version>
		</includes>
		<includes>
	<Version rdf:about="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::7:1:1">
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="./7/1/1/"/>
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="#bjmns:7:1:1"/>
		<identifier rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#NCName">c·x</identifier>
		<index rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">1</index>
		<fullTitle xml:lang="en">C(x)</fullTitle>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/hubs/86c4fe6afa05691fd8b3de265be0f78f"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/hubs/e3909dca25ea3cccbbd1f95567ce8dff"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/works/14075923"/>
		<dc:abstract rdf:parseType="Resource">
			<contents rdf:parseType="Literal"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en" xml:lang="en">
	<p>The important thing to see here is actually one of the accompanying notes, <a href="https://go.KIBI.family/Corpora/bjmns.tumblr.com,2013/7/1/:notes/The_Ballpoint_Pen-Tyneland/" resource="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::7:1::notes:The_Ballpoint_Pen-Tyneland"><code>bjmns:7:1::notes:The_Ballpoint_Pen-Tyneland</code></a>, which is probably my first genuine attempt at extensive worldbuilding.  Compare <a href="https://go.KIBI.family/Corpora/bjmns.tumblr.com,2013/7/Forces/" resource="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::7:Forces"><code>bjmns:7:Forces</code></a> for more on the various influences on this work.</p>
</div></contents>
		</dc:abstract>
