	</Version>
		</includes>
		<includes>
	<Version rdf:about="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::7:1:Flame">
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="./7/1/Flame/"/>
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="#bjmns:7:1:Flame"/>
		<identifier rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#NCName">Flame</identifier>
		<index rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#NCName">Flame</index>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/works/2615279"/>
		<dc:abstract rdf:parseType="Resource">
			<contents rdf:parseType="Literal"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en" xml:lang="en">
	<p>This was an early attempt at a darker, more political story with suspense and intrigue.  From reading the author’s note, apparently there was some <a href="http://id.loc.gov/resources/works/2615279"><code>lcbw:2615279</code></a> influence?  I couldn’t say.</p>
	<p>Elements of the conflict would eventually develop into <a href="https://go.KIBI.family/Corpora/bjmns.tumblr.com,2013/17/" resource="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::17"><code>bjmns:17</code></a>, although the plot itself would be mostly left in the rubbish bin.</p>
</div></contents>
		</dc:abstract>
